File: Eskom expects power constraints throughout the week because of the cold front. JOHANNESBURG - Despite its best efforts to get generators back up and running, Eskom says load-shedding will continue on Monday. Planned power cuts returned this weekend after a number of generating units broke down. UPDATE: Eskom announces Stage 2 load-shedding Stage two load-shedding will resume at 9 on Monday morning, and continue until 10pm. Eskom expects power constraints throughout the week because of the cold front. The power utility is urging people to use electricity wisely.